AMERICAN actor Tom Cruise is gracing Mzansi with his presence. Mr Mission Impossible, as he’s affectionately known, is in Hoedspruit, Limpopo shooting a movie with a film crew. Limpopo Tourism Agency posted pictures of the movie star on social media and welcomed him to the country. They also thanked him and his crew for choosing Limpopo. ALSO READ : LERATO MVELASE CELEBRATES 28 YEARS OF ACTING! “Here in Limpopo province, it will be Mission very much possible. Not Mission Impossible. A warm welcome to Tom Cruise and the entire film crew who are in Hoedspruit shooting a movie. Thank you for choosing our iconic destination to feature in the movie, from Hollywood to Hoedspruit and the rest of the world. #GoLimpopo MoreToEnjoy,” they wrote. A Twitter fan posted a video of Tom flying a helicopter around Oribi Gorge, KZN last Thursday, 10 February. He is allegedly in the country to film Mission Impossible 8 set to be released in 2024. Mission Impossible 7 will be released next year. These are said to be the last two films of the franchise he’ll star in as he ends his journey as the lead actor in the role of Ethan Hunt. Later this year, one of the most anticipated films, The Woman King, starring Viola Davis, Thuso Mbedu, Makgotso M, Zozibini Tunzi and Angelique Kidjo will also be filmed in Mzansi. A post shared by Limpopo Tourism Agency (@go_limpopo)